JOHANNESBURG - The condition of anti-apartheid struggle stalwart Ahmed Kathrada, 87, had deteriorated in the last 24 hours, his foundation said on Monday afternoon.Kathrada was admitted to hospital in Johannesburg earlier this month for surgery to ease blood clotting on the brain.The Ahmed Kathrada Foundation s director, Neeshan Balton, said that the veteran had experienced several post-operation complications, rendering his condition serious . Kathrada has contracted pneumonia, which has affected both his lungs, Balton said in a statement.WATCH: Night vigil for Ahmed Kathrada Despite appropriate medical care, his condition is deteriorating. He is currently comfortable. The Kathrada Foundation will keep the public informed on a regular basis about Kathrada s condition. Follow our Twitter handle @KathradaFound for updates, Balton added. We continue asking for your prayers during this period, both for Mr Kathrada and his family and friends.Learners from Victoria Primary School in KZN wish #Kathrada well! pic.twitter.com/iYolNSiMlQBalton said that members of the public were welcome to post their messages of support on the foundation s Facebook page leave cards bearing messages of support, or flowers, at the foundation s offices at Signet Terrace Office Park in Lenasia. All of the messages that we have received will be collated and passed on to the family, Balton explained.Kathrada, a tireless activist for non-racialism and constitutionalism, is one of three Rivonia trialists still alive today; the other two being Andrew Mlangeni and Denis Goldberg.#Kathrada latest with @ImanRappetti outside the hospital where he is being treated. More on #eNCA throughout the evening. pic.twitter.com/B8KbQL1wBJeNCA